      "name": "NIH bench hemolysis comparison — five VAD operating points",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in vitro measurements at five flow-speed combinations representative of VAD operation. Monte Carlo 95th-percentile prediction interval overlaps measured values at all five points; mean signed error is +18% (conservative over-prediction). Worst-case point (5 L/min, 3500 RPM) shows 31% over-prediction, within the ±35% adequacy criterion.",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-2022",
